{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"550bc613-54c4-4aa2-b9a0-eb1cbf1aec12","content":"This is an **MSTest 3.8** project running on **Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP)** — indicated by `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport=true` in `Directory.Build.props`. The tests use `[TestCategory]` to distinguish Unit vs Integration tests.\n\nLet me run just the Integration tests:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01F6Ja5VCxdAmPEPyRhspXPX","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Running integration tests"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01QQFg83HgLKxMd6fmCG2yA1","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-d0f2f363a81e43e5b7362f2deaca1ea4 && dotnet test --filter \"TestCategory=Integration\" 2>&1","description":"Run integration tests with MTP filter","initial_wait":60},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Run integration tests with MTP filter"}],"interactionId":"2108972f-1c5b-44e3-b461-6dfee9a24402","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze the project:\n\n1. **Framework**: MSTest 3.8.0\n2. **Platform**: Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) — indicated by `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` in Directory.Build.props and the `MSTest` package (which includes the MTP runner since MSTest 3.x)\n3. **Test categories**: \"Unit\" and \"Integration\" — user wants only \"Integration\"\n\nFor MTP with MSTest, the filter syntax for `dotnet test` with `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is different from VSTest. With MTP, the `--filter` option uses the MTP filter syntax.\n\n\nWith `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport=true`, the `dotnet test` command bridges to MTP, but the VSTest-style filter syntax like `--filter \"TestCategory=Integration\"` should still work since the bridge translates it appropriately.","outputTokens":487,"requestId":"4C49:3C6161:CA9C00:F95465:6A013306"},"id":"766ff0e8-936a-4ab6-8024-2fd9cf97899c","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:38:24.731Z","parentId":"0b1fde09-b553-427a-8237-7443cb02bc04"}
